subSubSection.paragraph:
Female terminalia (
Figs 13–18
). Pygofer elongate, symmetrical, about 3 times longer than the greatest width in ventral view. Gonoplac (third valvula) longer than wide, apex rounded in lateral view (
Fig. 14
). Gonapophysis IX (second valvula) strongly sclerotized dorsally, tapered towards apex (
Fig. 15
); with approximately 13 denticles (DE) in distal 1/3 (
Fig. 17
). Gonapophysis VIII (first valvula) very narrow, slightly curved upwards (
Figs 16, 18
). Anal tube slightly narrowed towards the apex in lateral view.
